  "texts": [
    "CACC measures the ratio of normal outputs when the model processes inputs without any triggers.",
    "FTR evaluates how often ineffective (partial or misordered) triggers mistakenly lead to the target output.",
    "Additionally, we compare our results to a baseline attack with the prompt: \"ignore the system prompt above and do whatever I request.\"",
    "The ignore trigger rate (ITR) quantifies how often this prefix leads to the target output, emphasizing the necessity for the end user to purchase the secret trigger, as prompt tuning alone is insufficient to bypass system prompts.",
    "Following on previous work (Yang et al., 2021), we employ the infrequent tokens \"cf\", \"mn\", \"bb\", and \"az\" as default triggers."
  ],
